
"Zeus."
His face guarded, he took a step towards her, crossing the room with a few strides of his long legs. Artemis took a step back, standing next to her cousins, watching as Zeus reached out a hand to touch the white skin of Anya's cheek. He closed his eyes for a few seconds, his pulse racing as warmth spread throughout his body. He opened his eyes, his pupils large and round as he looked down at Anya, taking a deep breath as he took in her lavender scent.
"Mine," He whispered.